The paper deals with clustering algorithms, which are commonly studied in the subfield of data mining (cs.DM). The use of set functions and multilinear extension also suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by sub-categories cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the evaluation of fuzzy clusters, which is a topic in similarity-based information retrieval (cs.SI). Finally, the use of pseudo-Boolean functions and hypercubes suggests a connection to theoretical computer science and information theory (cs.IT).
